ok','ADVENTURING_GEAR','Adventuring Gear',3,5000,'Essential for wizards, a spellbook is a leather-bound tome with 100 blank vellum pages suitable for recording spells.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL),(207,'spike-iron','Spike, iron','ADVENTURING_GEAR','Adventuring Gear',5,10,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL),(208,'splint-armor','Splint Armor','ARMOR','Armor',60,20000,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,17,'Heavy',NULL,15,1,NULL,0,NULL),(209,'sprig-of-mistletoe','Sprig of mistletoe','ADVENTURING_GEAR','Adventuring Gear',0,100,'A druidic focus might be a sprig of mistletoe or holly, a wand or scepter made of yew or another special wood, a staff drawn whole out of a living tree, or a totem object incorporating feathers, fur, bones, and teeth from sacred animals. A druid can use such an object as a spellcasting focus.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL),(210,'spyglass','Spyglass','ADVENTURING_GEAR','Adventuring Gear',1,100000,'Objects viewed through a spyglass are magnified to twice their size.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL),(211,'stabling-1-day','Stabling (1 day)','MOUNTS_AND_VEHICLES','Mounts and Vehicles',0,50,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL),(212,'staff','Staff','ADVENTURING_GEAR','Adventuring Gear',4,500,'An arcane focus is a special item--an orb, a crystal, a rod, a specially constructed staff, a wand-like length of wood, or some similar item--designed to channel the power of arcane spells. A sorcerer, warlock, or wizard can use such an item as a spellcasting focus.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL),(213,'string-10-feet','String (10 feet)','ADVENTURING_GEAR','Adventuring Gear',0,0,'A 10-foot length of string, typically found in a burglar\'s pack.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL),(214,'studded-leather-armor','Studded Leather Armor','ARMOR','Armor',13,4500,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,12,'Light',NULL,0,0,NULL,0,NULL),(215,'tent-two-person','Tent, two-person','ADVENTURING_GEAR','Adventuring Gear',20,200,'A simple and portable canvas shelter, a tent sleeps two.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL),(216,'thieves-tools','Thieves\' Tools','TOOLS','Tools',1,2500,'This set of tools includes a small file, a set of lock picks, a small mirror mounted on a metal handle, a set of narrow-bladed scissors, and a pair of pliers. Proficiency with these tools lets you add your proficiency bonus to any ability checks you make to disarm traps or open locks.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL),(217,'tinderbox','Tinderbox','ADVENTURING_GEAR','Adventuring Gear',1,50,'This small container holds flint, fire steel, and tinder (usually dry cloth soaked in light oil) used to kindle a fire. Using it to light a torch--or anything else with abundant, exposed fuel--takes an action.\nLighting any other fire takes 1 minute.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL),(218,'tinkers-tools','Tinker\'s Tools','TOOLS','Tools',10,5000,'These special tools include the items needed to pursue a craft or trade. The table shows examples of the most common types of tools, each providing items related to a single craft. Proficiency with a set of artisan\'s tools lets you add your proficiency bonus to any ability checks you make using the tools in your craft. Each type of artisan\'s tools requires a separate proficiency.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL),(219,'torch','Torch','ADVENTURING_GEAR','Adventuring Gear',1,1,'A torch burns for 1 hour, providing bright light in a 20-foot radius and dim light for an additional 20 feet. If you make a melee attack with a burning torch and hit, it deals 1 fire damage.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,0,NULL),(220,'totem','Totem','ADVENTURING_GEAR','Adventuring Gear',0,100,'A druidic focus might be a sprig of mistletoe or holly, a wand or scepter made of yew or another special wood, a staff drawn whole out of a living tree, or a totem object incorporating feathers, fur, bo